record_data.record_title: Spot Black Start Service Rate Schedule
record_data.record_plain_text: Spot Black Start Service Rate Schedule 1. Spot Black Start Service. Spot Black Start Service is a service that Helix Ravenswood, LLC ( Helix Ravenswood ) provides by operating, maintaining and testing certain critical equipment that is capable of starting generating facilities without the availability of an outside electric supply in order for those generating facilities assist in system restoration after a system-wide blackout. Helix Ravenswood s critical equipment will be operated, maintained and tested under the terms of this Spot Black Start Service Rate Schedule or Rate Schedule such that they are capable of starting Steam Units 10, 20 and 30 without the availability of an outside electric supply. The actual generation and sale of electric energy produced by Units 10, 20 and 30 a system-wide blackout is not included within the scope of Spot Black Start Service under this rate schedule. The sale of such energy is conducted pursuant to Helix Ravenswood s market based rate authority and commission approved rate schedule Original Sheet Nos. 1, 2 and 3, filed in Docket No. ER10-2860-000. Energy is sold either through bilateral agreements or the energy market operated by New York Independent System Operator, Inc. ( NYISO ). 2. Applicability. This Rate Schedule is applicable to all entities that elect to purchase Spot Black Start Service from Helix Ravenswood and which execute an agreement in the form of the pro forma service agreement attached hereto in Appendix No. 1. Service under this rate schedule shall be available on a month-to-month basis. A customer electing to purchase Spot Black Start Service under this rate schedule shall be required to purchase, as a block, the entirety of the Spot Black Start Service Helix Ravenswood provides for the applicable month. 3. Spot Black Start Operation, Maintenance and Testing Procedures. The purpose of operating, maintaining and testing Helix Ravenswood s critical black start equipment in accordance with the procedures established under this rate schedule is to gain experience and to assure as reasonably can be ascertained consistent with Good Utility Practice that the equipment will operate properly during an actual black out. Appendix No. 2 to this rate schedule sets forth the list of equipment that will be operated, maintained and tested as well as the parameters of the tests that Helix Ravenswood will conduct. All operation, maintenance and testing applicable hereunder shall be conducted on a weekly, monthly or annual basis. Appendix No. 3 to this rate schedule sets forth the operation, maintenance and testing procedures Helix Ravenswood will follow in furtherance of this rate schedule. Appendix Nos. 2 and 3 contain Critical Energy Infrastructure Information ( CEII ) as defined at 18 C.F.R. 388.113(c)(1), and therefore are on file with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ( Commission ) on a non-public basis pursuant to 18 C.F.R. 388.112. 4. Compensation. a. Fixed payments A Customer taking service under this rate schedule shall compensate Helix Ravenswood at the rate of $79,166.67/month. b. Variable Costs In addition to the fixed payments referred to above, a Customer taking service under this rate schedule shall reimburse Helix Ravenswood for all variable costs associated with Helix Ravenswood providing Spot Black Start Services. The monthly Spot Black Start Services payments shall include compensation for operator training costs, labor costs, fuel costs, and other legitimate, verifiable, and adequately documented costs associated with operation, maintenance and testing under this rate schedule applicable to the month in which a Customer takes service. Testing is conducted on a weekly and/or monthly basis, except for one test that is conducted on an annual basis. The variable costs associated with the annual test will be billed monthly at 1/12th the total cost. c. Other A Customer taking service under this rate schedule also shall reimburse Helix Ravenswood for the cost of equipment damage incurred during the month in which the Customer takes service under this rate schedule: (1) that resulted from conducting the tests required by this Rate Schedule; (2) where insurance does not cover such damages; and (3) that would not have occurred but for Helix Ravenswood s provision of Spot Black Start Services under this Rate Schedule. 5. Record Keeping Requirements Helix Ravenswood will maintain records of all cost information, test results, operation and maintenance information associated with providing Spot Black Start Services under this Rate Schedule. Such records contain CEII as defined at 18 C.F.R. 388.113(c)(1). Such records also may contain information, the disclosure of which could cause Helix Ravenswood competitive harm. To the extent a Customer desires to review Helix Ravenswood s records in furtherance of the audit rights described in Section 7 hereof, it may designate up to five reviewing representatives (for each of the two categories of information referred to in the preceding paragraph) to review such records. Each such representative shall be required to execute the non-disclosure certificate attached hereto in Appendix No. 4 in order to review CEII. Each such representative shall be required to execute the non-disclosure certificate attached hereto in Appendix No. 5 in order to review information the disclosure of which could cause Helix Ravenswood competitive harm. To the extent Helix Ravenswood concludes, based upon test results or operation and maintenance problems, that a generating unit identified in Section 1 will not be able to generate electric energywithout the availability of an outside electric supply, and therefore will be unable assist in system restoration after a system-wide blackout, it shall provide such information to NYISO on a confidential basis. In order that such information be communicated to NYISO as expeditiously as reasonably can be accomplished under the circumstances, NYISO at all times shall have on file with Helix Ravenswood executed non-disclosure certificates in the forms required by Appendix Nos. 4 and 5 of atleast one then-current NYISO employee. 6. Billing and Payment. When Helix Ravenswood provides Spot Black Start Service in a given month, the Customer that contracted for that service shall be billed for all fixed payments and variable and other costs applicable to the month for which it contracted for such service. Helix Ravenswood will provide an invoice to the Customer no later than fifteen (15) days following the end of the calendar month in which the service is provided. Customers under this rate schedule shall be required to submit payment to Helix Ravenswood no later than 30 days from the date an invoice is issued. Any payments received after this period will be charged interest at a rate calculated in accordance with 18 C.F.R. 35.19a (2009). All invoices shall be paid by electronic funds transfer, or by other mutually agreeable method(s), to the account designated by Helix Ravenswood. 7. Audit Rights Helix Ravenswood shall permit a Customer, at such Customer s expense, to inspect Helix Ravenswood s records concerning testing and maintenance applicable to the month in which the Customer contracted for service under this rate schedule. Such inspection shall take place at the Ravenswood plant site, and/or at Helix Ravenswood s offices at One Tower Center, 21st Floor, East Brunswick, NJ 08816, as Helix Ravenswood determines based upon the location of the records the Customer wishes to review. Such inspection may take place at a reasonable time and during normal business hours as mutually agreed to by Helix Ravenswood and Customer. A Customer exercising its rights of inspection hereunder agrees to maintain the confidentiality of all information Helix Ravenswood discloses to it in accord with the non-disclosure certificates contained in Appendix Nos. 4 and/or 5 as applicable. A Customer exercising its rights of inspection hereunder agrees that it will not use the confidential information for any purpose other than for the purposes of inspection hereunder. 8. Billing and Payment Disputes. Payments will be made subject to refund. A Customer shall have fifteen (15) days to review an invoice. In the event a Customer has questions regarding the propriety of the amount charged, the Customer shall have fifteen (15) days from the date it receives an invoice in which to contact Helix Ravenswood and request additional information necessary to understand the basis for the amount charged. Helix Ravenswood will make a good faith effort to respond within fifteen (15) days to any Customer requests for additional information. To the extent a Customer continues to have questions regarding the propriety of the amount charged following its receipt of additional information, it shall have fifteen (15) days to request to inspect the records applicable to the month in which it received service. The Customer s right to inspect records shall be governed by Section 7 hereof. 9. Resolution of Billing and Payment Disputes. If following an inspection conducted pursuant to Section 7 a Customer continues to question the propriety of the amount charged, senior management of the Customer (subject to its execution of the nondisclosure certificates contained in Appendix Nos. 4 and/or 5, as applicable) and Helix Ravenswood will engage in good faith efforts to attempt to resolve any outstanding issues within a period of thirty (30) days. If upon the conclusion of the thirty (30) day period, the senior management of the Customer and Helix Ravenswood have been unable to resolve the dispute concerning the invoice, the Customer shall have an additional forty-five (45) days in which to file a complaint with the Commission under FPA Section 206 in an effort to resolve the dispute. All information and records submitted with the complaint that is confidential under Section 5 hereof shall be submitted to the Commission strictly on a non-public basis, and Customer shall accord such information and records the same degree of confidentiality as is otherwise applicable under this rate schedule. If the Customer fails to file such a complaint with the Commission within the forty-five (45) day period, the amount set forth in the invoice shall be final and not subject to review. If the Customer files a timely complaint and the Commission issues a Final Order in favor of the Customer, Helix Ravenswood will calculate and issue to the Customer the amount of refund as determined by the Commission, inclusive of interest at a rate calculated in accordance with 18 C.F.R. 35.19a (2009).

record_data.record_title: Market-Based Sale of Capacity, Energy and Ancillary Services
record_data.record_plain_text:
RAVENSWOOD OPERATIONS, LLC Market-Based Sale of Capacity, Energy and Ancillary Services
1. Availability. Ravenswood Operations, LLC ("Seller") makes firm capacity and/or energy and non-firm energy and/or capacity available under this Rate Schedule to any purchaser for resale.
2. Applicability. The Rate Schedule is applicable to all wholesale sales of firm capacity and/or energy and non-firm energy and/or capacity by Seller.
3. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller.
4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller.
5. Effective Date. This Rate Schedule shall be effective on the date specified by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
6. Ancillary Services.
a. RTO/ISO Specific.
i. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection.
ii. New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc.
iii. New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), and operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc.
b. Third Party Provider.
Third-party ancillary services: Seller offers Regulation and Frequency Response Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, and Operating Reserve-Supplemental. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation and Frequency Response Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.
7. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller or pursuant to rules governing the NYISO.
8. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff.
9. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: N/A.
10. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 2 seller in the Northeast Region, and a Category 1 seller in all other Regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. Section; 35.36(a).
